text: Chutani‌ ‌is a vassal tribe of Muslim people which often entitled as name of clan‌ found among the lower‌ caste‌ ‌of ‌Julaha weavers‌ in the Gujarat state and other rehabilitated semi-arid villages, However they are pre-accountably emended among the _chutani sept_ of Khosa tribe of Jadgal. == Related pages == * Jadgali language * Indian Muslims * Islam in India == References == Category:Castes Category:Social groups of Punjab, India
title: Chutani (caste)
